Sequence.documentation:
'PPV' holds the phase to phase voltage phasors [V], as follows:
•	'PPV.[phsAB,phsBC,phsCA].cVal.[mag,ang].f' are phase voltage phasors; 
•	'PPV.angRef.stVal' is the quantity used as reference for the phase angles of the 3 phasors above.

'A' holds the currents [A] for three phases, as follows:
•	'A.[phsA,phsB,phsC].cVal.[mag,ang].f' are phase current phasors; 
•	'A.neut.cVal.[mag,ang].f' is neutral current phasor; 
•	'A.net.cVal.[mag,ang].f' is net current phasor (phsA+phsB+phsC+neut); 
•	'A.res.cVal.[mag,ang].f' is residual current phasor (phsA+phsB+phsC); 
•	'A.angRef.stVal' is the quantity used as reference for the phase angles of the 6 phasors above.
